For someone like me who literally dreads a visit to a dentist - the visit to Dr Ganesh Shetty's clinic was an absolute pleasure. I was diagnosed with a heavily "impacted" lower wisdom tooth that needed to be extracted. The initial diagnosis suggested that the procedure would be take 45 minutes (usually 15 minutes), but we were all surprised when the tooth was more impacted and submerged within the bone cavity than initially expected therefore extending the entire procedure to almost 2 hours! Usually one would expect both the doctor and the patient to freak out in such circumstances. However, Dr Shetty was cool as a cucumber and kept taking me through the process in a way that made me feel comfortable too. This I believe is the greatest quality that a surgeon needs to have and Dr Shetty definitely does. All thats well ends well, and so did the surgery. I am still in the process of recovering but the healing (I had sutures placed for 10 days) is fast and I am confident that its only a matter of days that I am completely back to normal.

I would highly recommend Dr Ganesh Shetty as a trusted and experienced surgeon to anyone in need for a top notch dental/oral procedure.

PS: I criss-cross 30 Kms and 90 minutes of traffic to meet Dr Shetty and its definitely worth it.

Not sure how they evaluate their patients. Some get previliged treatment and others don't. The only reason I chose to go to Dr.Ganesh was due to the ratings. Will seriously suggest not to fall for it. I would not go to his clinic if I am going to be attended by a junior doctor. I shouldn't be commenting on their capability but just didn't feel comfortable with the way they dealt with me.

Here are a few pointers before you visit them:
- Ratings: Don't fall for the ratings unless you are attended by Dr.Ganesh himself (which didn't happen in both my visits) 

- Appointments: don't bother booking an appointment on practo they don't care about the time - you might be made to wait for atleast 1 hour or even more(that's what happened in my case)

- Pricing: On the higher side, but you wouldn't mind if you will have a senior doctor attend to or do your procedure.

All in all just not a very nice experience for me. Hope they internalise this feedback and ensure they fix this for patients that will visit them in the future.

I would definitely NOT recommend Dr. Ganesh to anyone in the future. I was given an anesthetic injection and made to wait for more than an hour. Then Dr. Ganesh tried to pull my tooth out and it was extremely painful. He gave me another injection and I could feel the prick. That is when I realized and told him that the anesthetic effect had completely faded. I think a good doctor would have known for how long the anesthetic is effective. He later tried to extract my tooth and gave up half way through and said that he can't go ahead since I was not cooperating. I would really like to meet the person whose tooth was pulled out without being administered the anesthetic injection and still cooperated with Dr. Ganesh. I asked him to take an x-ray to see why it was so painful. He refused to do that which I think is a protocol for all dentists to follow before pulling out the wisdom tooth. I pleaded with him 4 to 5 times to try again but he was very adamant and would just not listen. I felt I was ditched and left to suffer. I finally had to rush to another dentist, with heavily bleeding gums, who was kind enough to understand my plight and successfully treated me immediately.
